[SN]TITLE[SN]
Giant sinkhole opens up in Italian street

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A giant sinkhole has opened up in Naples, in Italy.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
24 February 2015 Last updated at 09:07 GMT
The huge hole is 10 metres (33 ft) wide and has forced more than 300 people to leave their homes for safety.
A smaller crater first appeared a few days ago, but a broken water pipe and heavy rain made the ground to give way, creating a larger crater.
